name: printed wiring board production, mounted mainboard, desktop computer, Pb free | printed wiring board, mounted mainboard, desktop computer, Pb free | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/1091/documentation

This dataset represents the average composition and production efforts for 1 kg of a motherboard used in a desktop PC. It is based on a typical Desktop PC mainboard, used in modern computers. Main data are taken from the literature and own dismantling activities. Infrastructure and production efforts are based on own assumptions.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]

From reception of printed wiring board at the factory gate.

This dataset includes component input and production efforts (incl. PWB waste due to failure in mounting) for the production of Desktop PC mainboards, using Pb-containing solder material.
category: C:Manufacturing/26:Manufacture of computer, electronic and optical products/261:Manufacture of electronic components and boards/2610:Manufacture of electronic components and boards

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data represent a global valuable composition of Desktop PC mainboards.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Average PWB mounting technology (solder paste production line)

exchanges.description:
The motherboard is the largest circuit board (printed wiring board) in a PC. It contains the microprocessor(s) with heat sink, solid-state random access memory (RAM), support chips, Basic Input/Output System (BIOS), backup battery, etc. Many motherboards include built-in modems, sound, video, Ethernet, SCSI host adapters, RAID, Firewire, and other options. The fabrication of a printed wiring board is described in more details in part II (“modules”) of this report.
